-Cook the pasta in boiling water for about 8 minutes
-Strain the pasta and put it in a pan
-Add about half a cup of milk, depending on how creamy you want it to be
-Add around a tablespoon of butter
-Cook for a minute until butter melts, and the milk is warm
-Add around 4-5 handfuls of cheese to the pan
-Stir, and cook until cheese completely melts

